version.description:
Released in October 2010, Unicode 6.0 was the first version of the Unicode Standard to support emoji.

Some characters in prior versions of Unicode were retroactively updated to provide an emoji presentation. This release was the first to introduce new characters for the sole purpose of compatability with emojis being used in Japan.

apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the one o'clock emoji is a clear and simple clock face, showing the hour hand precisely pointing to the '1' with the minute hand at the '12'. Apple's design language renders it with a clean, bright face and subtle 3D shading that gives it a polished, easy-to-read appearance. This emoji is universally understood to represent the time one o'clock, often used for scheduling or indicating a specific moment.
